    "For ambiguous names, like abbreviations, we tie comments to these names, aiding models in understanding context.",
    "For large tables, a \"coarseto-fine\" approach is adopted: we initially filter values using the BM25 index based on the question and further refine them with the longest common substring algorithm.",
    "Using these techniques, we frame prompts for the CodeS model, enhancing schema linking and boosting text-to-SQL performance for complex databases.C3: How to adaptively transfer to databases within a new domain?",
    "In real-world applications, we aim for the CodeS model to adapt across various domains.",
    "A significant obstacle, however, is the lack of specific (question, SQL) pairs for fine-tuning."
